oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Jimmy Miller
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Jimmy Miller posed outdoors, wearing riding pants and high laced boots.

Photograph belonged to Edna Mays Miracle Liming. Born Sept. 25, 1906 near Cumberland Gap, Tennessee, Edna was the daughter of James Mays and Alice Lawson Mays. The surname of her first husband was Miracle, her daughter Unis Evalyn Miracle died shortly after birth in 1925. Edna later married Homer Liming in Oakland County, Michigan in 1930.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Edna Mays Miracle Liming Family Photographs, ca. 1880s-1920s
